Package entities

Class Appointment

java.lang.Object
entities.Appointment
public class Appointment extends Object
The Appointment class represents an appointment between a patient and a doctor. It includes details such as the appointment ID, doctor ID, date, time, status, service, medication name and status, and additional notes.

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(String appointmentID, String doctorID, String patientID, LocalDate date, LocalTime time, String status, String service, String medName, String medStatus, String notes)
      Constructs a new Appointment with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - the ID of the appointment
      doctorID - the ID of the doctor associated with the appointment
      patientID - the ID of the patient associated with the appointment
      date - the date of the appointment
      time - the time of the appointment
      status - the status of the appointment (eg "Unbooked", "Pending Confirmation", "Completed")
      service - the service provided during the appointment
      medName - the name of the prescribed medication
      medStatus - the status of the medication (eg "Dispensed", "Pending")
      notes - additional notes about the appointment
